    },
    {
      "id": "Xref",
      "code_hash": "0b4bdda5ced0cbc450f5791c17876e8b",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h2 id=\"usb-descriptor-hierarchy\">USB Descriptor Hierarchy</h2>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">USB devices are organized in a tree structure: Device \u2192 Configuration \u2192 Interface \u2192 Endpoint.</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Device contains: Vendor ID, Product ID and List of Configuration.<br>\nConfiguration: Are modes, like High power or Low power mode, most devices have only one mode. <br> Interface: Inside one configuartion, there are multiple interfaces. each represents a unique function. <br>\nExample: webcam has, Interface 0: Video camera, Interface 1: microphone, Interface 2: Speaker etc. <br>\nEndpoint: The Endpoints for each Interface/function: <br> IN endpoint: from device to computer. <br> OUT endpoint: from computer to device. <br> Types: Bulk(large package), interrupt(small packages), Isochronous (streaming data)</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
    {
      "id": "SFPL",
      "code_hash": "cd75561ba78dee69ea3e0e0a47b1015f",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><h2 id=\"how-to-figure-out-deviceid-and-vendorid\">How to figure out DeviceID and VendorID</h2>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">command on linux: lsusb</span>\n<h3 id=\"output\">Output:</h3>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Bus 001 Device 001: ID 1d6b:0002 Linux Foundation 2.0 root hub<br>\nBus 001 Device 002: ID 04f3:0c4c Elan Microelectronics Corp. ELAN:ARM-M4<br>\nBus 001 Device 004: ID 346d:5678 ITE Intenso Rainbow Line<br>\nBus 002 Device 001: ID 1d6b:0003 Linux Foundation 3.0 root hub<br>\nBus 003 Device 001: ID 1d6b:0002 Linux Foundation 2.0 root hub<br>\nBus 003 Device 002: ID 0bda:2852 Realtek Semiconductor Corp. Bluetooth Radio<br>\nBus 004 Device 001: ID 1d6b:0003 Linux Foundation 3.0 root hub<br></span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">its always after the ID &lt; VendorID : DeviceID &gt; <br>\nour Fingerprint device here is, the ELAN:ARM-M4, VendorID:04f3 DeviceID:0c4c</span></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
